Twin Birth Dataset (1989–1991)

Source:
National Bureau of Economic Research (NBER)
Linked Birth / Infant Death Data (Vital Statistics Data)

Original data sources:
http://www.nber.org/data/linked-birth-infant-death-data-vital-statistics-data.html

Specific files used:
http://www.nber.org/lbid/1989/linkco1989us_den.csv.zip
http://www.nber.org/lbid/1990/linkco1990us_den.csv.zip
http://www.nber.org/lbid/1991/linkco1991us_den.csv.zip

Dataset Guide:
http://www.nber.org/lbid/docs/LinkCO89Guide.pdf

Reference:
Almond, Douglas, Kenneth Y. Chay, and David S. Lee.
"The Costs of Low Birth Weight."
The Quarterly Journal of Economics, 120(3), 1031–1083, 2005.

Description:
This dataset contains information on twin births in the United States between
1989 and 1991. The data includes covariates such as parental characteristics,
health conditions, and birth outcomes for twin pairs.

License / Usage:
The original data is provided by the National Bureau of Economic Research (NBER).
Users should follow the terms and conditions specified by NBER for the use of
Linked Birth / Infant Death Data.

This copy is distributed for research and educational purposes only.
Users should cite the original data source and the reference paper when using
the dataset in academic work.